HEADWORD: Chokeberry
<hw>Choke"ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The small apple-shaped or pear-shaped fruit of an American shrub
(<spn>Pyrus arbutifolia</spn>) growing in damp thickets; also, the
shrub.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

